<TITLE> Rail links with Sylhet restored </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moulavibazaar, Oct 09 (bdnews24.com)Rail communications from Sylhet to Dhaka and Chittagong were restored some four hours after the links snapped when a cargo train derailed in Moulavibazar at Friday noon. Abdul Aziz, assistant station master of Srimangal, said a rescue train from Kulaura pulled up the two carriages to resume normal service. Inter-city Paharika Express left for Chittagong from Shamsher Nagar Station and Kushiara Express for Akhaura from Kulaura station, he added. The carriages rolled off the tracks between Komolganj Vanugachh and Shamsher Nagar stations, Foyzur Rahman, assistant station master of Srimangal, told bdnews24.com. "Two carriages of 908 (down) cargo train went off the tracks around 12pm between VanugachhShamsher Nagar stations of Sylhet-Akhaura railway section," he said. bdnews2
